NAME
    ls - list directory contents

SYNOPSIS
    ls [-1adhRrSt] [path...]

DESCRIPTION
    Lists files and directories. Defaults to current directory.
    Directories are shown with a trailing slash.

OPTIONS
    -l      Long format (permissions, size, date)
    -a      Show hidden files (starting with .)
    -1      One entry per line
    -h      Human-readable sizes (1K, 2M, 3G)
    -R      Recursive listing
    -S      Sort by size (largest first)
    -t      Sort by modification time (newest first)
    -r      Reverse sort order
    -d      List directories themselves, not contents

EXAMPLES
    ls
        List current directory

    ls -la
        Long format with hidden files

    ls -lhS /api/data
        Long format, human sizes, sorted by size

    ls -R /api/data
        Recursive listing of all models

    ls -1 *.json
        One per line with glob pattern

    ls -lt /tmp
        Sort by time, newest first

    ls -d */
        List only directories

SEE ALSO
    find, cd, pwd, tree
